<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAVORITE 'NATION' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tom Shales is flogging the message because he doesn't like the messenger ("TV 
Nation: Making a Point or Just Making Fun?," TV Times, Aug. 7). The only people 
humiliated on Michael Moore's "TV Nation" (NBC) are the ones who think they're 
acting in a reasonable manner but aren't.No one has to go before Moore's 
cameras! In doing so, they humiliate themselves. 
</P>
<P>
 The NAFTA piece updated us as to what's gone on since NAFTA passed. The 
segment on the cab drivers passing the "good" black guy in favor of the "bad" 
white one doesn't make fun of anyone. It just highlights how stupid racial 
stereotypes are. We didn't find the story about the Prairie Correctional 
Facility critical of the citizens who built it. We found it an example of the 
spend-craziness of lobbying the government for new facilities when others are 
available. 
</P>
<P>
 We appreciate this worthwhile program but fear that unjust panning by Shales 
will get it scrapped in favor of more mindless entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee and Liz Newman, Bell Canyon 
