<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAPERBACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 PORTRAITS OF NATIVE AMERICANS: 23 Postcards from the Field Museum photographs 
by Charles Carpenter (The New Press: $9.95; 48 pp., paperback original). During 
the 1904 Louisiana Purchase Exhibit (the fair Judy Garland visits in "Meet Me 
in St. Louis"), indigenous peoples from around the world were displayed in 
artificial villages like zoo animals. It's surprising that these dignified 
portraits emerged from that setting. Carpenter obviously respected his subjects 
and sympathized with their plight: His emotions remain evident 90 years later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
