<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITIC'S PICK: 'BAD BEHAVIOUR' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kenneth Turan 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Les Blair's 1993 film offers a comic look at a love relationship that is 
wearing thin around the edges and makes few demands other than asking that we 
settle in for the duration. While it lacks the bite of fellow Brit Mike Leigh's 
films, it shares with them an ability to put strongly drawn folks on the 
screen. Beautifully acted by Sinead Cusack and Stephen Rea (pictured, with 
Saira Todd), Gerry and Ellie McAllister are an amusingly realistic 
married-with-two-children couple, frustrated by the patterns of their lives 
(Cinemax Monday at 4:35 a.m.). Kenneth Turan 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Television Review 
</P>
</TYPE>
