<DOCNO> LA082894-0112 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 073865 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
August 28, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Calendar; Page 61; Calendar Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
333 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP MUSIC CHARTS: SELF-ESTEEM BUILDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Offspring's "Smash" has been a Southern California smash for some time, 
residing at the upper levels of The Times pop album chart--No. 3 this week. But 
the Orange County band's album is also doing well nationally, climbing into the 
Top 10, at No. 10. This could be the one that cracks the soundtrack barrier at 
the top of the Southern California chart, where "The Lion King" and "Forrest 
Gump" have been 1-2 for weeks. Neil Young's album "Sleeps With Angels," which 
is getting rave reviews, is off to a fast start with fans too, debuting at No. 
5 on the Southern California pop chart. TOP 10 ALBUMS 03,04,38,11 Title, Artist 
(Nat'l Rank) Last Week 1 The Lion King, soundtrack (1) 1 2 Forrest Gump, 
soundtrack (2) 2 3 Smash, Offspring (10) 3 4 Dookie, Green Day (5) 7 5 Sleeps 
With Angels, Neil Young (9) -- 6 August...After, Counting Crows (6) 4 7 Purple, 
Stone Temple Pilots (4) 5 8 The Sign, Ace of Base (3) 6 9 Superunknown, 
Soundgarden (11) 9 10 Regulate...G-Funk Era, Warren G. (7) 8 TOP 10 SINGLES 
03,04,38,11 Title, Artist (National Rank) Last Week 1 I'll Make Love..., Boyz 
II Men (1) 1 2 Stay, Lisa Loeb and Nine Stories (3) 2 3 Stroke You Up, Changing 
Faces (4) 9 4 Funkdafied, Da Brat (5) 3 5 Fantastic Voyage, Coolio (2) 4 6 Bop 
Gun, Ice Cube (21) 7 7 I Swear, All-4-One (6) 6 8 When Can I See You, Babyface 
(10) 5 9 This D.J., Warren G. (7) 8 10 100% Pure Love, Crystal Waters (31) 11 
TOP 10 R&B ALBUMS 03,04,38,11 Title, Artist (National Rank) Last Week 1 
