RECORD RACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Randy Lewis 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *** David Ball, "Thinkin' Problem," Warner Bros. Ball's debut album recalls 
the golden age of honky-tonk, focusing almost exclusively on the ghosts of 
busted relationships and the accompanying feelings of all-consuming failure.His 
wondrous voice at times echoes past greats more than it creates its own stamp, 
but Ball's willingness to forge his own path is unmistakable. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 Randy Lewis 
</P>
