<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jean Rosenbluth 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *** Jeffrey Gaines, "Somewhat Slightly Dazed," Chrysalis/EMI. The delicious 
power-pop bounce that reverberates through this album is not what you'd expect 
from a musician whose debut was a serene, largely acoustic affair.But the 
Philadelphia singer-songwriter defies expectations by drawing from Elvis 
Costello and the Bangles as deftly as he once evoked the guitar-strumming, 
protest-singing troubadours of the previous generation, with equally pleasing 
results. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 Jean Rosenbluth 
