<P>
RECORD RACK: IN BRIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Randy Lewis 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ** Crosby, Stills & Nash, "After the Storm," Atlantic. After a storm, 
everything's either fresh and lush or just plain soggy.Though this is just the 
trio's sixth studio album in 25 years, CSN might well have spent a bit more 
time toweling off before stepping back into the studio. The love songs are 
generally less drippy than the weighty social commentary. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 Randy Lewis 
</P>
