<TEXT>
<P>
 *** Edie Brickell, "Picture Perfect Morning," Geffen. Never mind Michael and 
Lisa Marie -- here's Brickell with hubby Paul Simon, whose versatile production 
puts several new spins on Brickell's airy voice and bohemian songs.Most 
surprising are a few pleasant forays into classic soul ballad territory, with 
perhaps the ultimate odd coupling on "Good Times," a silky number with a guest 
appearance by basso romantico Barry White. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent).  
</P>
