<P>
 ** 1/2 BLACKstreet, "BLACKstreet," Interscope. Group founder Teddy Riley is 
still regarded as one of hip-hop's innovative young honchos.However, no tracks 
here really equal past hits he produced for Guy, Bobby Brown and Keith Sweat. 
Songs such as "Baby Be Mine" and "Booti Calls" are irrepressibly funky, but 
their casually cynical attitudes toward sex are questionable. 
</P>
