<TEXT>
<P>
 COURTNEY CONTINUED: Speaking of Love on-line, the singer, whose messages have 
frequently been deleted by America Online monitors due to profane or 
inflammatory language, was understandably outraged when a note from a service 
user making lewd remarks about Love's daughter was allowed to remain on the 
service for more than a week before being deleted. 
</P>
<P>
 "That's clearly a violation of our terms-of-service agreement," says AOL 
spokeswoman Pam McGraw of the lewd note. "But we have thousands of message 
areas and each is monitored by its own staff." Steve Hochman 
</P>
