<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Steve Hochman 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 WIN SOME, LOSE SOME: The L.A. House of Blues has apparently scored a big coup 
with word that the club will host Eric Clapton in a rare, intimate appearance 
for three or four nights in mid-November. Clapton's spokeswoman was unable to 
confirm the booking, but sources at the club and in the concert promotion 
industry say that the shows will be part of a brief U.S. club tour Clapton will 
do before mounting a full series of arena shows (including a Nov. 3 stop at the 
Forum). 
</P>
<P>
 On the down side, the House of Blues seems to have lost a chance at a special 
show by Steely Dan when it botched the dinner reservation of the band's 
management at the recent Boz Scaggs show. Sources at the club say that HK 
Management, which also handles Scaggs, withdrew an offer for a Steely Dan 
appearance after the incident. An HK spokeswoman says that the idea of a Steely 
Dan booking had never gone beyond mere conversation, and that the company is 
planning future bookings at the House of Blues for other clients, including 
Michael McDonald in December. Steve Hochman 
</P>
</TEXT>
