<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARTYRS MUSEUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding Anne Bergman's article "Creating a Synergy Along the Miracle Mile" 
(Aug. 14), she omitted a real gem, Martyrs Memorial and Museum of the 
Holocaust. It is located on the first and second floors of the Jewish Community 
Building at 6505 Wilshire Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 The founders of the museum, most of whom are Holocaust survivors, established 
the museum with the mandate to commemorate, preserve and educated the public 
about the history of the Holocaust.  
</P>
<P>
 Admission is free and the museum is open Monday-Thursday, 9 a.m.-5 p.m., 
Friday from 9 a.m.-3 p.m. and Sunday noon-5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 LILLIAN GOLDMAN, chair 
</P>
<P>
 Friends of Martyrs Memorial 
</P>
<P>
 and Museum of the Holocaust 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
