<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: MISCELLANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The state Department of Labor and Industries in Washington gave King County 
the go-ahead to resume ceiling repairs inside the Kingdome. 
</P>
<P>
 All repair work had been halted since Aug. 17, when two workers died in the 
collapse of a construction crane inside the stadium. The Kingdome has been 
closed since July 19, when four acoustical ceiling tiles fell into empty stands 
before a scheduled Mariner game. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Bruce Baumgartner and Melvin Douglas of the United States advanced to the 
semifinals of the World Freestyle Wrestling Championships at Istanbul, Turkey. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Willie Cauley, a Pittsburgh forward, was jailed for nearly two months in 
upstate New York this summer for criminal mischief and harassment, Big East 
Briefs magazine reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief; Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA082894-0140 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 073893 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
August 28, 1994, Sunday, Southland Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 24; Column 2; National Desk 
</P>
