NATION IN BRIEF; GEORGIA; TED TURNER HAS LIP SKIN CANCER EXCISED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Broadcasting executive Ted Turner announced at a graduation ceremony in 
Atlanta that he has skin cancer, then left, saying he was scheduled for 
surgery.Turner, 55, was to give the keynote address at Georgia State 
University's commencement, but he spoke for less than five minutes. "I'm going 
straight from here to a skin cancer operation," Turner told the students and 
their families. "The one piece of advice I can give you is put on sunscreen and 
wear a hat." A small cancerous growth on his lip was removed in an Atlanta 
doctor's office. A spokesman said his prognosis was good. 
</P>
