NATION IN BRIEF; GEORGIA; FBI PROBING FIRM OVER MEDICAL BILLING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The FBI is investigating several Atlanta doctors tied to a home health care 
company that has been accused of inflating the medical bills of critically ill 
patients, including AIDS patients. An article in the Atlanta 
Journal-Constitution quoted FBI officials as confirming the existence of the 
probe amid publicity over a civil lawsuit that charges Caremark International 
Inc., two Atlanta doctors and a local pharmacy with charging "unconscionable" 
sums for their services. The suit was filed last April by Michael Alan Booth, 
who entered the care of two Atlanta AIDS specialists after being diagnosed with 
the disease. 
</P>
