NATION IN BRIEF; THE WEST; HOMES DAMAGED IN OREGON FOREST FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents of a rural canyon near Sams Valley in southwestern Oregon were 
barred from returning to inspect the damage to burned-out homes as a stubborn 
forest fire swelled to 7,250 acres.Across the West, 24 major fires still 
burning had covered 391,200 acres in Oregon, Washington, California, Idaho and 
Montana, according to the National Interagency Fire Center in Boise, Ida. The 
Hull Mountain fire in southwestern Oregon detroyed four houses and eight other 
buildings, said U.S. Forest Service spokesman Chris Friend. Firefighters 
estimated that the blaze, about 15 miles northwest of Medford, would be 
contained late Monday. 
