<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRAUDE TENDS TO GLAMOROUS BRENTWOOD, IGNORES VAN NUYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 You recently reported about Brentwood and all the wonderful things Councilman 
Marvin Braude has done for San Vicente Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 This is astounding to me, since Mr. Braude's district includes the area on Van 
Nuys Boulevard from Magnolia Boulevard up to Sherman Way, one of the most 
unsightly areas in the Valley.I have lived here for over 40 years and have done 
most of my shopping on Van Nuys Boulevard, until the last few years when the 
nice shops left and we have nothing but tacky stores with tacky signs and 
merchandise displayed on the sidewalks. 
</P>
<P>
 Perhaps Mr. Braude should take a trip from Brentwood, where he lives, to Van 
Nuys Boulevard, where he is supposed to be in charge. 
</P>
<P>
 To quote the article, "Low density, beauty and substantial public benefit, 
that's what I'm concerned about," Mr. Braude said. So take a good look at Van 
Nuys Boulevard, Mr. Braude's bailiwick, and you wonder how he can sleep at 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 MRS. HELEN SONGER 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys 
