<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: LAW: TV PROGRAM ADDRESSES ABUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles City Atty. James Hahn will discuss domestic abuse Monday on cable 
television government access channels serving the city. 
</P>
<P>
 The program, "When Home is Hell," will include interviews with victims, 
batterers and law enforcement officials.The programwill air at 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Ted Goldstein, executive producer of the program and communications director 
for the city attorney's office, said about 20,000 domestic family-violence 
cases are prosecuted by the city attorney's office each year. 
</P>
<P>
 "Domestic family violence is a major factor in criminal misdemeanor cases. We 
want to inform the public that the city attorney's office is vitally concerned 
with domestic family violence, and we vigorously support prosecution of 
batterers, providing shelters for the victims and counseling for batterers," 
Goldstein said. 
</P>
