<HEADLINE>
<P>
11TH DISTRICT COST OF FUNDS INDEX DOWN SIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I take issue with Robert J. Bruss' comments regarding the 11th District Cost 
of Funds index.("Is Adjustable Rate Loan Better Than Fixed Rate?" Real Estate 
Q&A, Aug. 14). 
</P>
<P>
 There are other viable adjustable indexes that are also lagging indicators 
that move as or even more slowly than the costs of funds, for example, Bank of 
America's 12 Month Treasury Average Index. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, Bruss neglected to mention that the majority of 11th District Cost of 
Funds loans have negative amortization, which means that loan balances can 
increase rather than decrease. 
</P>
<P>
 LINDA M. COTA-KUMAGAI, Loan Officer, Bank of America, Encino 
