<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIMES READERS ACT ON TRUST ARTICLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On behalf of Scripps Foundation for Medicine and Science, I would like to 
thank Betty Lukas for her article on charitable remainder trusts in the May 22 
issue of The Times. 
</P>
<P>
 Two of your subscribers read the article on that Sunday evening and called 
their attorney on Monday morning.By Friday of that same week, we had met with a 
wonderful couple, their attorney and their accountant. By the following Friday, 
their $4 million home had been appraised, put in a trust, listed with the 
realtor, and our new donors were on their way to a new home in Maine. 
</P>
<P>
 Now, they will receive income for life as soon as the home sells, avoid over 
$600,000 of capital gains taxes and over $2 million of estate taxes, and 
receive a current income tax deduction of over $1 million. 
</P>
<P>
 They are also very pleased that at the end of their lives a magnificent gift 
may help find a cure for inflammatory bowel disease. 
</P>
<P>
 RON TIMMONS, Associate Vice President, Scripps Foundation for Medicine and 
Science, La Jolla 
