<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE FIND MOVIE PROP, NOT BOMB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Police Department's Bomb Squad was called out to a salvage lot 
to investigate a possible bomb Saturday only to find a movie prop, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 At noon, an employee of Pick Your Parts salvage yard in the 11200 block of 
Pendleton Street reported that a pipe bomb was found in an abandoned car on the 
lot. The bomb squad was notified and hundreds of customers were evacuated from 
the five-acre lot with the help of a police helicopter, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 After two hours of examining the two bricks marked C-4, the bomb squad 
"determined them to be movie props," said Sgt. Joe Flores of LAPD's Foothill 
Division. 
</P>
