<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: MID-CITY AREA; JOINT REDEVELOPMENT MEETING PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The seven project area committees that voted last month to consolidate their 
efforts into one large redevelopment zone will meet jointly at 3:30 p.m. 
Tuesday in the multipurpose room of Pio Pico Elementary School, 1512 S. 
Arlington Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Representatives of the seven commercial corridors will discuss the next steps 
in forming a redevelopment zone: preparing a draft preliminary plan and forming 
one elected joint-project area committee for the entire zone, which will 
oversee drafting and implementing a redevelopment program. 
</P>
<P>
 Committee members will begin prioritizing projects and pinpointing 
redevelopment goals, said Community Redevelopment Agency spokeswoman Gail 
Anderson. 
</P>
<P>
 The commercial corridors forming the tentative redevelopment zone include the 
Greater Mid-City Revitalization Area, which is bounded by San Vicente Boulevard 
on the north, Venice Boulevard on the south, West Boulevard on the east and La 
Brea Avenue on the west, as well as commercial strips along Jefferson, Adams, 
Washington, Crenshaw, Pico and Venice boulevards.  
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 766-9830. 
</P>
</TEXT>
