<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; NORTH KOREA; PYONGYANG REJECTS REACTOR FROM SOUTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 North Korea has rejected a South Korean offer to provide it with a modern 
reactor, threatening efforts to resolve the Korean nuclear crisis, Seoul 
officials said.The South Korean offer is "an intolerable insult" with "a 
sinister political purpose," North Korea said in radio reports monitored in 
Seoul and Tokyo. Giving North Korea reactors is a key part of a U.S.-North 
Korean deal earlier this month aimed at resolving suspicion the North is 
developing nuclear weapons. American negotiators agreed to help North Korea get 
modern reactors and give it some form of diplomatic recognition in exchange for 
Pyongyang's promise to freeze its nuclear program. 
</P>
