<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; MALAYSIA; PREMIER SAYS JAPAN OWES NO APOLOGIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Malaysia's leader stunned Japanese Prime Minister Tomiichi Murayama by 
declaring that Tokyo should stop apologizing for World War II and start being a 
world leader in keeping the peace. With his comments, Prime Minister Mahathir 
Mohammed leaped head-first into a roiling domestic debate in Japan, 
embarrassing his guest by highlighting major policy differences within 
Murayama's ruling coalition. 
</P>
