<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL STRIKE: DEVELOPMENTS FROM DAY 16 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Games lost: 14. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total games lost: 209. 
</P>
<P>
 * Games remaining: 460. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total income lost by players: $70.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Estimated revenue lost by owners: $136 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Key development: None and no negotiating sessions are scheduled. 
</P>
<P>
 * In quotes: "Right now, we're trying to fit in with the owners and understand 
all the issues. But at some point in time you're going to see the Colorado 
Rockies say, 'Hey, this is ludicrous.' At some point you're going to see us 
step up and become a more vocal player." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Charlie Monfort Owner, Colorado Rockies 
</P>
