<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE NATION; REVIVED NEBRASKA FACES WEST 
VIRGINIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nebraska, ranked No. 4 in the preseason Associated Press poll and one of the 
national championship favorites this season, takes on No. 24 West Virginia 
today in the Kickoff Classic at Giants Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Haunted by a history of big-game flops, the undefeated Cornhuskers entered the 
last Orange Bowl as 17-point underdogs to top-ranked Florida State, then 
outplayed the Seminoles before losing, 18-16, when a last-second field-goal 
attempt sailed wide. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think the Orange Bowl changed the public perception of Nebraska," said 
offensive tackle Rob Zatechka. "It didn't change us, but it changed what people 
thought about us." 
</P>
