<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL '94 / SEASON PREVIEWS; LAMBRIGHT DID LITTLE TO STOP GARRETT'S 
RUN FOR HEISMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In USC's Heritage Hall, Mike Garrett's Heisman Trophy rests in a display case, 
along with those won by Charles White and Marcus Allen.  
</P>
<P>
 O.J. Simpson's was on display, until it was stolen July 28. 
</P>
<P>
 Washington football Coach Jim Lambright, who played for Washington in the 
mid-1960s, says he deserves to have a small piece of Garrett's Heisman, after a 
contribution he made in the 1965 USC-Washington game at Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was a 180-pound outside linebacker then, and Garrett came right for me, 
made a great move to the outside -- and he just froze me," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 "I sort of crumpled forward, and fell on my face. Garrett went for about 70 
yards. I looked pretty comical in the films on Monday, and everyone had their 
laughs." 
</P>
<P>
 USC won the game, 34-0.  
</P>
<P>
 Garrett is now USC's athletic director. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
