<P>
PRO FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; RAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coach Chuck Knox bristled when asked if Maddox's $875,000 contract money might 
have been better spent on acquiring offensive linemen, a troubled spot for the 
Rams in the exhibition season. 
</P>
<P>
 "We made an offer sheet on Kevin Donnalley (of Houston) this spring," Knox 
said."We make some mistakes like everybody else, but if there was a bona fide 
offensive lineman out there, the money would not be a concern." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 New Ram quarterback Tommy Maddox got a chuckle Friday night when he saw Tampa 
Bay quarterback Trent Dilfer, bypassed by the Rams in last April's draft, 
lining up behind the right guard to take a snap. 
</P>
<P>
 "That shouldn't be too hard to learn," said Maddox, who saw Dilfer's gaffe on 
a TV highlights show. "I hope he has been lining up behind center for most of 
his career. That shouldn't be too hard." MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
