<HEADLINE>
<P>
PARADISE CREEK HEADS ARLINGTON MILLION FIELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Paradise Creek heads a field of 14 grass-course runners in today's Arlington 
Million at Arlington International Racecourse. 
</P>
<P>
 Paradise Creek won six consecutive stakes this year until being narrowly 
beaten by Lure in the Bernard Baruch Handicap at Saratoga. 
</P>
<P>
 His competition will include three horses from Europe, Muhtarram and Spartan 
Shareef from England and Petit Loup from France. 
</P>
<P>
 The others entered in the 1 1/4-mile race are Alex The Great, Blues Traveller, 
Fanmore, Fastness, Johann Quatz, Marastani, Mr. Cowboy, Semillon, Split Run and 
Star Of Cozzene. 
</P>
<P>
 Star Of Cozzene won the Million last year, leading Johannn Quatz to the wire, 
after finishing ninth to Dear Doctor the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
 No horse has ever won the Million in successive years. Star Of Cozzene is 
winless in three starts this year. 
</P>
<P>
 Paradise Creek, owned by Masayuki Nishiyama, is the 8-5 early favorite, 
followed by Muhtarram at 7-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
