<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: DIVISION I PLAYER TRANSFERS TO CSUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal State Northridge football team has added an NCAA Division I transfer 
who is expected to contribute at defensive end, Matador Coach Bob Burt said 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ken Freitas, who played at Claremont High, Citrus College and Utah State, was 
given his release by Utah State on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 He is expected to play immediately for the Matadors, Burt said. Freitas, a 
senior, is 6-feet-5, 235 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's a very good player," Burt said. "He'll fit in somewhere." 
</P>
<P>
 The Matadors, who conducted their annual intrasquad scrimmage Saturday, open 
the season Sept. 10 at Boise State. 
</P>
<P>
 A pair of freshmen walk-on players left the team this week. Defensive back 
Tyrone Francis, a Reseda High graduate, was declared ineligible and linebacker 
Erin Christianson of Morton Grove, Ill., left for personal reasons, Burt said. 
Football  
</P>
<P>
 Fast Action football is seeking team entries for its adult flag football 
league scheduled to begin Sept. 24. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 310-829-5226. 
</P>
</TEXT>
